1
00:00:01,793 --> 00:00:04,213
[theme music playing]

2
00:01:22,916 --> 00:01:28,839
MALICE

3
00:01:53,113 --> 00:01:54,573
[cheeping]

4
00:02:17,095 --> 00:02:19,806
[inaudible]

5
00:02:27,606 --> 00:02:30,275
COMING OF AGE CEREMONY
NHN NEWS 9

6
00:03:34,214 --> 00:03:38,051
[Gevanni] Near, it's all taken care of.
I did exactly as you asked.

7
00:03:38,760 --> 00:03:39,636
[Near] Good…

8
00:03:42,514 --> 00:03:43,724
[chains rattling]

9
00:03:45,308 --> 00:03:48,687
[pen scratching on paper]

10
00:03:51,523 --> 00:03:53,775
MATSUMOTO

11
00:03:59,614 --> 00:04:03,118
"T." That is all I have to tell you today.
We'll talk soon.

12
00:04:03,618 --> 00:04:05,203
[Mikami] Very well. I understand.

13
00:04:05,912 --> 00:04:07,789
I also have a message for you.

14
00:04:08,123 --> 00:04:09,624
[Takada] Yes. What is it?

15
00:04:10,125 --> 00:04:11,376
I've confirmed it.

16
00:04:11,668 --> 00:04:12,544
[gasps softly]

17
00:04:12,711 --> 00:04:15,464
[phone hangs up]

18
00:04:20,302 --> 00:04:21,887
[phone ringing]

19
00:04:22,137 --> 00:04:23,180
[Matsuda] You got a text?

20
00:04:23,680 --> 00:04:24,890
I WANT TO SEE YOU

21
00:04:25,015 --> 00:04:29,603
Ooh, it says she wants to see you!
Man, I'm so jealous. [sighs]

22
00:04:30,228 --> 00:04:34,524
[Light] I've done it. That's the sign
of confirmation from Mikami.

23
00:04:34,649 --> 00:04:38,570
Now, all I have to do is wait for Near
to request a meeting face to face.

24
00:04:38,653 --> 00:04:41,031
Game over, Near! I win.

25
00:04:41,615 --> 00:04:44,075
I knew what your move would be
from the very beginning.

26
00:04:45,035 --> 00:04:47,037
-[monitor beeps]
-Sir, this is Gevanni.

27
00:04:47,162 --> 00:04:49,414
I've been checking the notebook regularly
as you ordered.

28
00:04:49,790 --> 00:04:52,918
For the past three days, he's continued
filling out one page every night

29
00:04:53,001 --> 00:04:54,795
after midnight as he usually does.

30
00:04:55,003 --> 00:04:56,421
The victims still match up.

31
00:04:56,546 --> 00:04:59,007
And there's been no change
in Mikami's behavior otherwise.

32
00:05:00,050 --> 00:05:00,926
[Near] I understand.

33
00:05:02,177 --> 00:05:04,137
Well, then let's begin.

34
00:05:04,304 --> 00:05:07,641
[clock ticking slowly]

35
00:05:09,935 --> 00:05:10,852
[monitor beeping]

36
00:05:11,311 --> 00:05:12,646
It's Near!

37
00:05:13,063 --> 00:05:15,232
-[Light] He called!
-[Near] L?

38
00:05:15,816 --> 00:05:17,734
Yes, this is L. What is it, Near?

39
00:05:18,360 --> 00:05:19,861
[Near] I want to meet you.

40
00:05:20,320 --> 00:05:21,196
What?

41
00:05:21,780 --> 00:05:24,741
[Near] There is something I must show you
pertaining to the Kira case.

42
00:05:25,784 --> 00:05:28,995
[Light] But... don't you suspect me
of being Kira?

43
00:05:29,162 --> 00:05:31,790
Do you really think it's wise
to reveal your face to me?

44
00:05:32,165 --> 00:05:35,544
[Near] That's true. I cannot show you
unless I reveal my face.

45
00:05:35,794 --> 00:05:38,588
Furthermore, the very act
of showing my face will prove something.

46
00:05:39,130 --> 00:05:41,049
And that will bring this case to a close.

47
00:05:41,216 --> 00:05:42,133
[all gasp]

48
00:05:42,259 --> 00:05:43,260
All right, fine.

49
00:05:43,969 --> 00:05:47,347
As far as I'm concerned, the sooner you
realize you're wrong about me, the better.

50
00:05:48,056 --> 00:05:52,018
[Aizawa] The time has finally come
for Near to prove that Light is Kira.

51
00:05:52,185 --> 00:05:54,646
But on the other hand, if that's true,
this will be a chance

52
00:05:54,771 --> 00:05:58,149
for Light to kill Near.
It all comes down to this.

53
00:05:58,441 --> 00:06:00,819
[Near] I'd like to lay out
some ground rules for the meeting.

54
00:06:01,069 --> 00:06:03,238
[Light] We're willing to go along
with whatever you want.

55
00:06:04,781 --> 00:06:09,327
First, I wanna have all the investigators
from both teams be present.

56
00:06:09,494 --> 00:06:12,831
In other words, everyone who is chasing
after Kira should be gathered together

57
00:06:12,956 --> 00:06:14,124
to take part in the meeting.

58
00:06:14,791 --> 00:06:16,793
[Light] I understand.
That's not a problem.

59
00:06:17,168 --> 00:06:18,420
[Near] As I mentioned before,

60
00:06:18,545 --> 00:06:20,797
there are a total of four members
in the SPK.

61
00:06:21,089 --> 00:06:23,800
That's including myself.
All of us will be there.

62
00:06:24,134 --> 00:06:28,430
Besides our team, we'll also bring along
Mr. Mogi, who's currently staying with us.

63
00:06:29,097 --> 00:06:32,183
As for Miss Amane, she will be released
right before we meet.

64
00:06:32,392 --> 00:06:33,977
She'll not be told where we're going.

65
00:06:34,769 --> 00:06:38,273
You can come and meet us once you confirm
that she has been safely released.

66
00:06:38,607 --> 00:06:39,608
Is that acceptable?

67
00:06:40,025 --> 00:06:42,235
-[Matsuda] What do we do?
-Hmm.

68
00:06:42,611 --> 00:06:43,987
[Light] Okay, Near, I understand.

69
00:06:44,321 --> 00:06:47,115
I have a team of five investigators,
including myself.

70
00:06:47,490 --> 00:06:49,326
Of course, Mogi's with you
at the moment,

71
00:06:49,451 --> 00:06:51,494
so aside from me,
there'll be only three people.

72
00:06:51,912 --> 00:06:55,749
Very well. That's fine.
Now, as for our meeting place…

73
00:07:00,587 --> 00:07:04,424
Daikoku Wharf. There's a warehouse
on the outskirts of the southeast side

74
00:07:04,507 --> 00:07:07,969
that's been abandoned for some time.
It's known as the Yellow Box.

75
00:07:08,762 --> 00:07:11,306
I've already taken the liberty
of purchasing it.

76
00:07:11,514 --> 00:07:13,975
If this arrangement is fine with you,
then we'll use it.

77
00:07:14,434 --> 00:07:16,519
How about that, Light Yagami?

78
00:07:16,686 --> 00:07:19,689
With a location like this ,
you can do what you're planning to do.

79
00:07:20,273 --> 00:07:21,316
One more thing.

80
00:07:21,650 --> 00:07:23,234
This meeting cannot take place

81
00:07:23,401 --> 00:07:25,820
unless I have your word that someone
will bring the notebook.

82
00:07:26,196 --> 00:07:28,323
Huh? Wait, why the notebook?

83
00:07:28,573 --> 00:07:29,824
[Near] It's quite simple.

84
00:07:30,241 --> 00:07:34,204
If your entire team leaves HQ to meet me,
then there'll be no one left behind

85
00:07:34,287 --> 00:07:35,330
to guard the notebook.

86
00:07:35,664 --> 00:07:39,042
I can promise you this.
I will make no attempts to steal it.

87
00:07:39,584 --> 00:07:41,544
In fact, I won't even try to touch it.

88
00:07:41,962 --> 00:07:45,090
As long as Mr. Aizawa can confirm
that it's the genuine notebook,

89
00:07:45,215 --> 00:07:47,759
I'm willing to place my faith in you
and accept his word.

90
00:07:47,926 --> 00:07:48,885
Huh?

91
00:07:49,219 --> 00:07:50,095
All right.

92
00:07:50,178 --> 00:07:53,598
However, I do insist that someone
other than L hold onto it.

93
00:07:54,015 --> 00:07:57,602
My reasons for making that request
should be fairly obvious to you.

94
00:07:58,061 --> 00:08:01,773
Right, I understand. But I'll be the one
who decides who will hold onto it.

95
00:08:01,898 --> 00:08:02,941
Does that sound fair?

96
00:08:03,191 --> 00:08:07,153
[Near] Yes, of course. Then all that's
left to arrange is the time and date.

97
00:08:07,362 --> 00:08:09,739
[Light] Right. The question is, what time?

98
00:08:10,699 --> 00:08:13,034
[Near] Mikami makes his judgments
after midnight.

99
00:08:13,201 --> 00:08:15,036
He most likely receives a notice
in the morning

100
00:08:15,203 --> 00:08:16,663
of which people to kill next.

101
00:08:17,038 --> 00:08:18,957
If we take his movements
into consideration...

102
00:08:21,459 --> 00:08:25,505
Say... three days from now,
on the 28th at 1:00 p.m.?

103
00:08:26,256 --> 00:08:30,051
[Light] One o'clock, huh? That's the exact
time I expected him to pick.

104
00:08:30,260 --> 00:08:33,138
Near is obviously aware
of Mikami's movements.

105
00:08:33,680 --> 00:08:37,434
That's fine by me.
The time doesn't really concern us.

106
00:08:38,476 --> 00:08:41,062
[Near] Well, then. One o'clock.
Three days from now.

107
00:08:41,187 --> 00:08:42,188
[Light] Sure.

108
00:08:44,357 --> 00:08:45,275
[Light] Near.

109
00:08:45,400 --> 00:08:46,776
[Near] Light Yagami.

110
00:08:47,277 --> 00:08:49,404
[both] I know exactly what your plan is!

111
00:08:49,654 --> 00:08:51,614
[both] And I'm going to win!

112
00:08:57,370 --> 00:09:01,124
Kiyomi, I'm sorry, but I'm a little busier
than usual today.

113
00:09:01,458 --> 00:09:04,461
Oh, really? Does that mean
you can't stay until morning?

114
00:09:04,669 --> 00:09:06,421
Yeah, I'm sorry.

115
00:09:06,629 --> 00:09:07,922
The police are gonna have
their hands full

116
00:09:08,006 --> 00:09:09,424
for the next two to three days.

117
00:09:10,258 --> 00:09:11,342
That's a shame.

118
00:09:14,637 --> 00:09:18,808
[Light] I've already given orders to both
Mikami and Takada about what to do.

119
00:09:19,017 --> 00:09:22,395
This will be the final order.
To kill Near.

120
00:09:22,562 --> 00:09:24,147
JANUARY 28 1:00 PM
DAIKOKU WHARF WAREHOUSE

121
00:09:42,040 --> 00:09:42,874
[camera shutter clicking]

122
00:09:55,386 --> 00:09:58,389
DEAR MS. TAKADA, I LOVE YOU!

123
00:10:07,774 --> 00:10:09,359
[engine revving]

124
00:10:09,442 --> 00:10:10,777
[tires screeching]

125
00:10:14,322 --> 00:10:15,615
Heads up, we're under attack!

126
00:10:15,698 --> 00:10:17,492
[Lidner] Quick! This way.
Are you all right?

127
00:10:17,617 --> 00:10:18,493
[Takada] Yes.

128
00:10:19,619 --> 00:10:21,329
[bodyguard] He's getting away! After them!

129
00:10:21,621 --> 00:10:24,082
[Lidner] We need to get inside NHN now.

130
00:10:24,165 --> 00:10:27,085
-[tires screeching]
-[Mello] Don't do it. Take a look around.

131
00:10:27,168 --> 00:10:29,963
It's not safer here. Not even inside.

132
00:10:30,505 --> 00:10:31,506
Mello!

133
00:10:32,215 --> 00:10:36,052
[Mello] It's best if you get her away
from here right now. Miss Takada, get on!

134
00:10:37,762 --> 00:10:38,763
Now!

135
00:10:39,222 --> 00:10:41,182
It's okay. You'll be safe with him.

136
00:10:41,307 --> 00:10:43,059
-Please. You have to go.
-[Takada] Right.

137
00:10:44,394 --> 00:10:45,270
[engine revving]

138
00:10:48,565 --> 00:10:51,276
Team A and team B,
stay on that bike's tail

139
00:10:51,401 --> 00:10:52,443
and don't lose sight of them.

140
00:10:52,944 --> 00:10:55,947
As for the rest of you,
I need you to find that assailant.

141
00:11:06,166 --> 00:11:08,168
All right! We've confirmed
Ms. Takada's safety.

142
00:11:08,501 --> 00:11:10,128
Let's get her into car number seven.

143
00:11:14,799 --> 00:11:16,676
[tires screeching]

144
00:11:17,969 --> 00:11:20,221
-What the hell?
-No, he's taking her!

145
00:11:20,763 --> 00:11:21,806
[bodyguard 1] Damn it!

146
00:11:22,473 --> 00:11:24,309
[bodyguard 2] Stop, you idiot!
You can't do that.

147
00:11:24,475 --> 00:11:26,019
What if it ends up hitting her?

148
00:11:28,229 --> 00:11:29,731
[stammering] What are you doing?!

149
00:11:56,090 --> 00:11:58,593
[reporter] One of the attackers
was heavily armed.

150
00:11:58,927 --> 00:12:00,220
TAKADA KIDNAPPED
IN FRONT OF NHN?

151
00:12:00,303 --> 00:12:01,471
As of this moment,
both Ms. Takada's escort team

152
00:12:01,554 --> 00:12:03,598
and the police are hot on the tail
of the suspects.

153
00:12:04,098 --> 00:12:06,351
[Matsuda] Oh, man. This is really bad.

154
00:12:06,517 --> 00:12:07,602
[Aizawa] Is it Near again?

155
00:12:08,269 --> 00:12:11,022
[Light] Near, you promised
that we'd meet in three days’ time.

156
00:12:11,147 --> 00:12:14,192
What's the meaning of making a move
like this now? It doesn't make sense.

157
00:12:14,484 --> 00:12:17,570
No, this isn't Near's style.
It's more like…

158
00:12:17,654 --> 00:12:18,613
[monitor beeps]

159
00:12:19,072 --> 00:12:20,198
[Light] It's Near!

160
00:12:21,115 --> 00:12:22,325
[horns honking]

161
00:12:28,790 --> 00:12:30,500
[indistinct yelling]

162
00:12:32,043 --> 00:12:35,129
[tires screeching]

163
00:12:40,510 --> 00:12:42,387
[Matt] So, those cars got ahead
of me, huh?

164
00:12:42,553 --> 00:12:45,223
How many damn bodyguards
does one woman need anyway?

165
00:12:50,019 --> 00:12:51,980
[Matt] Hey, come on! Give me a break.

166
00:12:52,272 --> 00:12:55,483
Since when were the Japanese allowed
to carry around such big guns?

167
00:12:55,608 --> 00:12:58,778
You got me. I'm part of this whole
kidnapping incident.

168
00:12:58,903 --> 00:13:01,030
That means you'll have a lot
of questions to ask.

169
00:13:01,864 --> 00:13:07,620
-You won't shoot--
-[guns firing]

170
00:13:15,795 --> 00:13:19,549
What an idiot. He probably wouldn't
have told us anything anyway.

171
00:13:19,924 --> 00:13:23,136
And death is the only way to pay
for crimes against Kira.

172
00:13:30,101 --> 00:13:30,977
[Takada] This man…

173
00:13:31,477 --> 00:13:35,857
He's the person that Light warned me
to be extra careful of. Mello.

174
00:13:36,524 --> 00:13:38,192
Mihael Keehl…

175
00:14:02,633 --> 00:14:04,010
[Takada whimpering]

176
00:14:08,306 --> 00:14:11,517
[Mello] Take off everything you're wearing
and put it all in that box.

177
00:14:17,315 --> 00:14:18,358
Hurry up.

178
00:14:19,275 --> 00:14:20,943
You can use this blanket.

179
00:14:26,115 --> 00:14:29,327
[Near] L, I am not the one
who kidnapped Takada.

180
00:14:30,244 --> 00:14:32,663
Is that so? Then it has to be...

181
00:14:33,039 --> 00:14:35,333
-Mello.
-[Near] Yes, that's right.

182
00:14:35,833 --> 00:14:37,543
I have to be honest with you on this.

183
00:14:37,752 --> 00:14:41,255
We had one of our members
escorting Takada and they confirmed it.

184
00:14:41,881 --> 00:14:43,716
Mello was the one who abducted her.

185
00:14:44,759 --> 00:14:48,262
I'm apologize for letting this happen
while one of us was guarding her.

186
00:14:48,388 --> 00:14:52,225
[Light] Near... isn't there any way
for you to contact Mello?

187
00:14:52,767 --> 00:14:54,811
[Near]
No, I'm afraid that would be impossible.

188
00:14:55,019 --> 00:14:56,854
While I do have a method
of getting in touch with him,

189
00:14:56,979 --> 00:14:59,399
there's no way he'd respond
in the current situation.

190
00:15:03,236 --> 00:15:04,654
[Takada] Before I take off the rest,

191
00:15:04,946 --> 00:15:07,698
could I please have the blanket
so I can wrap it around me?

192
00:15:10,701 --> 00:15:11,828
Whatever you want.

193
00:15:36,894 --> 00:15:38,312
NHN NEWS 7
LADY TAKADA KIDNAPPED

194
00:15:38,438 --> 00:15:39,605
Our latest report is that the escort team
was forced

195
00:15:39,689 --> 00:15:40,940
to shoot one of the perpetrators

196
00:15:41,065 --> 00:15:44,652
They are also still making efforts
to track Ms. Takada's whereabouts.

197
00:15:44,777 --> 00:15:46,279
[Ide] Were you able to get a hold of her?

198
00:15:46,988 --> 00:15:49,449
[Light] Not yet.
Takada's phone has been turned off.

199
00:15:49,532 --> 00:15:51,159
Mello must have confiscated it.

200
00:15:51,242 --> 00:15:52,660
-[phone beeps]
-Damn it.

201
00:15:52,743 --> 00:15:54,454
I need to get in touch with Takada.

202
00:15:54,662 --> 00:15:57,832
With no way of getting a hold of her,
all I can do is wait.

203
00:16:28,154 --> 00:16:30,781
[Mello] This is the only thing
that can be done.

204
00:16:30,907 --> 00:16:32,033
If I don't do it--

205
00:16:32,116 --> 00:16:34,535
[reporter] As for the suspect
who was gunned down earlier,

206
00:16:34,660 --> 00:16:37,997
we're still not able to identify him.
The police are tracking the remaining...

207
00:16:38,080 --> 00:16:41,125
[Mello]
Matt… I never thought you'd be killed.

208
00:16:42,460 --> 00:16:43,711
I'm sorry.

209
00:16:46,255 --> 00:16:48,549
[shivering]

210
00:16:54,764 --> 00:16:58,184
[panting]

211
00:16:58,351 --> 00:16:59,727
[phone ringing]

212
00:16:59,894 --> 00:17:01,854
-Light's cell phone!
-Could it be her?

213
00:17:02,021 --> 00:17:03,314
Quiet, everyone.

214
00:17:04,065 --> 00:17:04,941
Hello?

215
00:17:06,108 --> 00:17:08,236
[Takada sobbing] Light… I…

216
00:17:08,694 --> 00:17:09,904
-Ms. Takada?
-[all gasp]

217
00:17:10,613 --> 00:17:12,073
Listen to me, are you all right?

218
00:17:13,032 --> 00:17:15,910
The only reason she'd be able to call me
like this without getting caught

219
00:17:15,993 --> 00:17:19,247
is if she had an opportunity
to get away from Mello. Or...

220
00:17:19,789 --> 00:17:22,667
[Takada] Light, Light, please save me!

221
00:17:22,875 --> 00:17:26,128
[Light] It's all right. Calm down.
Answer my questions, okay?

222
00:17:26,295 --> 00:17:27,880
[sobbing] Okay.

223
00:17:29,382 --> 00:17:32,051
[Light] First, your location.
Do you know where you are?

224
00:17:32,468 --> 00:17:34,971
[Takada] No. No, I don't know where I am.

225
00:17:35,388 --> 00:17:39,225
I was put into a truck that was locked
from the outside.

226
00:17:39,934 --> 00:17:42,562
But we were on the freeway
and I caught a glimpse of a sign

227
00:17:42,687 --> 00:17:44,021
that said we were heading to Nagano.

228
00:17:45,022 --> 00:17:47,483
Right now, I think we're parked
inside of a building somewhere.

229
00:17:47,608 --> 00:17:50,152
[Light]
Miss Takada, you are Kira's spokesperson.

230
00:17:50,611 --> 00:17:53,364
Do you remember the conversation
we had when I told you

231
00:17:53,489 --> 00:17:56,325
that there might be people who would try
to hurt you because of that?

232
00:17:56,826 --> 00:17:58,536
[Takada] Yes, I remember.

233
00:17:59,412 --> 00:18:03,291
We talked about what you should do
if a situation like this ever arose.

234
00:18:03,457 --> 00:18:04,875
Do you remember that?

235
00:18:05,126 --> 00:18:06,294
[Takada] I remember…

236
00:18:07,044 --> 00:18:09,088
I did what you told me to, Light.

237
00:18:09,505 --> 00:18:10,423
I did it.

238
00:18:11,591 --> 00:18:12,675
[Light] Yes!

239
00:18:13,801 --> 00:18:16,429
[Takada] I didn't struggle,
even when he stripped me naked.

240
00:18:16,512 --> 00:18:18,431
I did exactly as you said.

241
00:18:18,598 --> 00:18:24,353
I made survival my first priority,
and-- and I did it.

242
00:18:27,898 --> 00:18:31,652
Please, Light, I did everything
that you told me to…

243
00:18:31,944 --> 00:18:34,322
Come quickly. Save me!

244
00:18:34,447 --> 00:18:35,323
[Light] Ms. Takada…

245
00:18:36,282 --> 00:18:38,909
You remember what I told you to do
after that, don't you?

246
00:18:40,453 --> 00:18:43,623
[Takada] I have to do as many killings
as possible while I still can.

247
00:18:44,165 --> 00:18:46,042
I... I know.

248
00:18:46,459 --> 00:18:48,085
-But Light--
-Can you do it?

249
00:18:49,378 --> 00:18:51,380
[whimpering]

250
00:18:54,842 --> 00:18:56,802
-[Takada] I can do it.
-[phone hangs up]

251
00:19:01,140 --> 00:19:02,850
[sobbing]

252
00:19:03,184 --> 00:19:05,686
Aizawa, Ide, let's get going.

253
00:19:06,145 --> 00:19:08,481
Matsuda, you stay here and take care
of headquarters.

254
00:19:08,564 --> 00:19:09,607
You got it.

255
00:19:11,651 --> 00:19:13,694
[sobbing]

256
00:19:19,825 --> 00:19:20,785
KYOTO LEGAL
GOVERNMENT BUILDING

257
00:19:20,868 --> 00:19:21,744
[Takada] It's me…

258
00:19:22,119 --> 00:19:24,830
Send me as many names of people
to punish as you can.

259
00:19:24,955 --> 00:19:26,082
Here's my email address.

260
00:19:26,374 --> 00:19:28,376
Yes. Right, I understand.

261
00:19:29,210 --> 00:19:32,213
If Takada is calling me like this,
it must mean that she's been able

262
00:19:32,296 --> 00:19:33,673
to kill her kidnappers.

263
00:19:33,881 --> 00:19:36,842
In which case, the only certainty
is that she's in a situation

264
00:19:36,967 --> 00:19:38,344
where she can't move.

265
00:19:40,429 --> 00:19:43,516
Nakajima, I'm going to go to the scene
of the crime for this case.

266
00:19:43,766 --> 00:19:44,642
[Nakajima] Okay.

267
00:19:46,310 --> 00:19:48,896
[Light] All right. I got the location
by tracing the call.

268
00:19:48,979 --> 00:19:50,648
Head to Karuizawa by freeway.

269
00:19:50,815 --> 00:19:54,568
[Aizawa] Karuizawa, huh? Damn. It'll take
at least 30 minutes to get there.

270
00:19:54,652 --> 00:19:57,321
[Light] Well, hurry.
This is Mello we're talking about.

271
00:19:57,405 --> 00:19:58,614
Who knows what he'll do?

272
00:19:58,906 --> 00:19:59,949
Got it.

273
00:20:03,494 --> 00:20:07,206
[Light] I don't believe this.
Aizawa and Ide are just too stupid.

274
00:20:07,289 --> 00:20:10,292
They jumped the gun and got
in the front seats without even thinking.

275
00:20:10,418 --> 00:20:13,295
-This is just too easy.
-[clicking]

276
00:20:19,927 --> 00:20:20,803
[gasps]

277
00:20:35,234 --> 00:20:36,277
-[gasps]
-[heart beating]

278
00:20:49,915 --> 00:20:50,791
[gasps]

279
00:20:57,006 --> 00:21:00,134
[Lidner gasps] No, no!

280
00:21:01,635 --> 00:21:03,304
What the hell is this?

281
00:21:10,436 --> 00:21:13,397
[Light] Kiyomi Takada, Suicide.

282
00:21:14,023 --> 00:21:18,778
January 26, 2013, 2:32 PM.

283
00:21:19,445 --> 00:21:23,032
Burns to death by setting fire
to everything around her…

284
00:21:23,741 --> 00:21:25,785
including everything she wrote on.

285
00:21:29,872 --> 00:21:36,796
TO BE CONTINUED

286
00:21:39,089 --> 00:21:42,134
[theme music playing]
